WALKER
v.
The N.C. STATE BOARD OF DENTAL EXAMINERS 95PA16-1 Supreme Court of North Carolina. September 22, 2016

Ryan McKaig, Attorney at Law, Elizabeth Brooks Scherer, Attorney at Law, Raleigh, For Walker, Cynthia (D.D.S.).

Carolin Bakewell, Attorney at Law, Matthew W. Sawchak, Attorney at Law, *221Stephen D. Feldman, Attorney at Law, Troy D. Shelton, Attorney at Law, Paul M. Cox, Attorney at Law, Raleigh, For The N.C. State Board of Dental Examiners.

Clinton R. Pinyan, Attorney at Law, Greensboro, For N.C. Board of Pharmacy.

The following order has been entered on the Motion for Extension of Time to File Two Reply Briefs filed on the 21st of September 2016 by Petitioner:

"Motion Allowed by order of the Court in conference, this the 22nd of September 2016."

Petitioner shall have up to and including the 14th day of October 2016 to file and serve his/her brief with this Court.
